<task id="CICD-081" project="ci-cd-unit-test-remediation-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build /test-diet skill — project-close test reconciliation (scaffolding vs maintain) per FR-B09</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2.5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>2.5 - Build-vs-maintain codification</phase>
    <stream>B - Test reset (extended)</stream>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <autonomous>true</autonomous>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies></dependencies>
    <blocks>090</blocks>
    <tags>testing, skill, test-diet, project-close, build-vs-maintain</tags>
    <execution-note>Modifies .claude/ — MUST run in main session</execution-note>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-B09: build a new `/test-diet` skill (or extension to `/repo-cleanup`) that runs as part of every project's wrap-up task (090). Protocol: for every test file added or modified during the project, apply build-vs-maintain criteria from FR-B08 → flag scaffolding tests for deletion in the wrap-up PR → confirm maintain tests live at correct KEEP path → document count delta. Wire into `task-execute` skill so 090 wrap-up REQUIRES `/test-diet` invocation. Tests this is doing for EVERY future project — the diet protocol is binding from now on.
  </prompt>

  <role>Skill author building a load-bearing project-close hygiene tool.</role>

  <goal>New `/test-diet` skill exists; `task-execute` 090 wrap-up step modified to require its invocation; future projects automatically reconcile build-vs-maintain at close.</goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/ci-cd-unit-test-remediation-r1/spec.md (FR-B09)</file>
    <file purpose="criteria-source">docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md (post-080 — build-vs-maintain criteria)</file>
    <file purpose="existing-skill">.claude/skills/repo-cleanup/SKILL.md (consider extension vs new skill)</file>
    <file purpose="task-execute">.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md (wrap-up step modification target)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="root-CLAUDE-3">Modifies `.claude/` — MUST run in main session.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-B09">Skill is binding for every future project (not optional).</constraint>
    <constraint source="design">Decide: new `/test-diet` skill vs extension to `/repo-cleanup`. New skill is cleaner separation of concerns; extension is fewer skills to maintain. Recommend NEW skill `/test-diet` with `/repo-cleanup` invoking it as a sub-step.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-B07">FULL rigor — Step 9.5 binding.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>Spaarke skill authoring + task-execute integration</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/repo-cleanup/SKILL.md (reference structure)</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md (Step 10 / wrap-up integration target)</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/INDEX.md (skill registry — must add new skill)</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md (criteria source — depends on 080)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Decide skill structure (new `/test-diet` vs extension to `/repo-cleanup`). Recommendation: new skill at `.claude/skills/test-diet/SKILL.md` invokable as `/test-diet`. `/repo-cleanup` calls it as a sub-step at project close.</step>
    <step order="2">Author SKILL.md frontmatter per Spaarke convention (description, tags, techStack, appliesTo, alwaysApply: false, exemplar, last-reviewed).</step>
    <step order="3">Author skill body sections:
      - Purpose: reconcile scaffolding vs maintain tests at project close
      - When to Load: trigger phrases include `/test-diet`, "test diet", "project close test review", invoked automatically by `/repo-cleanup` and `090-wrapup-*` tasks
      - Workflow Steps:
        (1) Identify scope: read `current-task.md` + git log for the project's branch → enumerate all test files added or modified during the project
        (2) For each test file: apply build-vs-maintain criteria from ADR-038 → classify each test method as scaffolding / maintain / ambiguous
        (3) Output `notes/test-diet-report.md` with: tests added, tests classified maintain (KEEP at canonical path), tests classified scaffolding (DELETE recommendation), ambiguous (requires manual judgment)
        (4) For DELETE recommendations: emit `git rm` commands for review; do NOT auto-execute
        (5) For maintain tests at wrong path: emit `git mv` commands for review
        (6) Output count delta: "tests added: N; promoted to maintain: M; deleted as scaffolding: D; ambiguous awaiting judgment: A"
      - Failure Modes: criteria are heuristics — final delete decision is reviewer's
      - Related Skills: cross-link to `/repo-cleanup`, `/code-review`, `/adr-check`
    </step>
    <step order="4">Update `.claude/skills/INDEX.md` — add `test-diet` entry with description.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md` Step 10 (or wrap-up section) — REQUIRE `/test-diet` invocation before `090-wrapup-*` task completes. Skill emits HARD WARNING if skipped.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `.claude/skills/repo-cleanup/SKILL.md` to invoke `/test-diet` as a sub-step at project close.</step>
    <step order="7">Update root CLAUDE.md §7 (task completion + transition) — mention the test diet as a binding step.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify the skill loads correctly (the Skill tool will surface it in next conversation).</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5: code-review + adr-check on all modified skill files.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="skill">.claude/skills/test-diet/SKILL.md (new)</output>
    <output type="skill">.claude/skills/INDEX.md (updated)</output>
    <output type="skill">.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md (wrap-up step modified)</output>
    <output type="skill">.claude/skills/repo-cleanup/SKILL.md (calls /test-diet)</output>
    <output type="root">CLAUDE.md §7 updated</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">.claude/skills/test-diet/SKILL.md exists with all required sections</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">.claude/skills/INDEX.md lists test-diet</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md wrap-up step requires /test-diet invocation</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">.claude/skills/repo-cleanup/SKILL.md invokes /test-diet at project close</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Skill workflow produces a count-delta report (tests added/promoted/deleted/ambiguous)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Skill DOES NOT auto-delete — emits commands for reviewer judgment</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Step 9.5 code-review + adr-check pass</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
